metadata.name: Toupie-Néon #82
metadata.description:
Multicolor particles sampling space in 2D to give birth to 3D shapes in rotation.
Put any rythmic music you like and watch it in a dark room till your retina is printed with psychedelic patterns.

My most complex generator in the ideas yet the simplest in implementation & most unpredictable in the results with high diversity and peculiar rarities.
It's cheap because I'd like to see many variations of this generator so mint a lot ;)

You can navigate the scene, snapshot it, fly over it or just watch it.

WARNING: Webgl/GPU strongly advised for smoothness, CPU/mobile compliant with certainly heavy lag. 2K/4K/8K resolutions will burn your GPU ;)

Controls:
- H: hide/show help.
- Click/Move mouse - orbit control
- Dblclick/Space - start/pause animation.
- I: hide/show info panel. Click for panels (info, FPS).
- A-Q/D - resolution down/up (720p, 1080p, 2K, 4K, 8K)
- S - export full resolution pix (up to 8K)
- W-Z/C - rotation speede down/up
- F - fly mode on/off
- X/V - fly speed down/up

Toupie-Néon @naibdian 2022 using Opensource WebGL, ThreeJS libs, Inigo Quilez FBM noise functions.

metadata.name: All Fold: Sketch #184
metadata.description:
'All Fold: Sketch' is a generative system intended to celebrate the writing and artwork that can only be found in the pages of a sketchbook. The project itself is much like a sketch, and attempts to represent the spirit of a work-in-progress.

The fold is included as a reminder that there is always another page.

In the context of the market, the pricing of this project is intended to offer an enjoyable minting experience, while giving the opportunity to contribute to important charities.

- 60% of any primary sales will be split between "Girls Who Code" and "Cure Parkinson's"
- 60% of any royalties will be split between "Girls Who Code" and "Cure Parkinson's"

The aesthetics of this project were directly inspired by the works of Gunta Stölzl, Anni Albers, Gertrud Arndt, Kenneth Martin, and Josef Albers.

Created by Eric Davidson. 2023.

metadata.name: Décollage #117
metadata.description:
A generative sketch based on the concept of décollage, an artistic process that involves cutting or tearing pieces of an original image. The resulting outputs bear a resemblance to artworks produced using the lacerated poster technique, where posters are layered and torn to reveal parts of the posters underneath.

In live mode, add &size=<YOUR_PIXEL_SIZE> to change the pixel size of the image for export (Right click to save). For example, &size=4000 will set the width of the image to be 4000 pixels. Note that this will not work with sizes beyond 5000 pixels.

(Allowlist is based on quantity of previous works owned).

metadata.name: regularity #22
metadata.description: This generative NFT created with three.js is an animated geometric masterpiece. The animation is a mesmerizing display of intricate shapes and patterns that move and morph in hypnotic ways, creating a stunning visual experience for the viewer. The geometry is complex and detailed, with an almost fractal-like quality to it, adding to the sense of depth and immersion in the artwork.

metadata.name: Agave & Patchwork #109
metadata.description:
Agave & Patchwork
---------------
Controls:
Press 1-6 to change the scale of the canvas (1 = default, 2000px x 2000px, 6 = 12,000px x 12,000px)
S: Save output at current size
F: Toggle fullscreen
Add the url params x and y to set custom dimensions. For example, add &x=1500&y=500 for a 1500px x 500px image
---------------
Tyler Boswell (@teaboswell) 2023
